cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SE

The paper introduces a new method for estimating probabilities in stochastic simulations, which is particularly suitable for multi-agent-based simulations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also mentions that the method can be applied to any type of simulation, which suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The method involves partitioning and selection, which are common techniques in the field of data structures and algorithms, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the method on a well-known MABS, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
